Floral cover up sleeve for Katia from Toronto! Thank you! 4 sessions in one week. Started with covering hand and forearm so that part is visibly healing and scabbing already. Accepting new artists and guests in Austin, Texas! We’re an open space which can be collaborative and educational at times but working more in private is an option as well. We’re looking for professional and like minded creatives and we are open to newcomers as there is opportunity for growth -must have 1 year experience! This is a safe space /all are welcome -Please bring: a sense of humor, honesty and loyalty! We’re looking forward to connect
Dm @burning.hand or email burninghandguest@gmail.com

one of those pieces I’ve been wanting to share detail shots and different angles. only showed the outer arm view so far.. from last year.

Eric’s wish was to cover his old work with daffodil flowers and trippy lines. I tried with a really light mix of grey as a foundation to achieve lots of contrast and it worked out great. Loving the silverish effect. All grey and all lines are healed and settled! Only the darker shading and the white in the flowers are fresh.
#nofilter #transformation #coveruptattoo

Head is always a big challenge! Thanks for the trust Anthony from MA! I had to cover up some older pieces on side and top of the head (last pic shows a little). Decided to break the symmetry and go with an organic flow. I had limited area as we he wished to keep the pieces on the back of his head and sides of the neck. video soon! All drawn on.

black on black and white on black for Frank from Seattle! Eventually it could use more white in some areas I think but today/tomorrow we’ll get to the other side where I have to work on top of the exact same tone and structure. 🦾🦾

#blackonblack #whiteonblacktattoo #coveruptattoo

Around 23 hours spread over 5 days for Frank from Seattle. Hope to blast over the the chest center in the future. What you see in the before pic is what I was working with.. several years old black out on arms and shoulder which was a great base for new black and white on top of it. Full view of his right arm (currently healing) in last post.
I’ll share more about the healing process soon. I have no problem with showing white on black healed and I’ve done it before. Sometimes it takes 2 passes for it to last. Not always easy to get healed shots with clients who live far away. But I’ll post a two years healed/settled one soon!
#blastovertattoo #whiteonblacktattoo
